!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

bulk /bʌlk/

(bulking,bulked,bulks) 

1. N-SING You can refer to something's bulk when you want to emphasize that it is very large. 大块 [书面] 

例： The truck pulled out of the lot, its bulk unnerving against the dawn. 拂晓时分，卡车驶出了停车场，庞大的车身看起来有点儿可怕。 

2. N-SING You can refer to a large person's body or to their weight or size as their bulk . 庞大肥硕的身躯 

例： Bannol lowered his bulk carefully into the chair. 班诺尔那肥硕的身躯小心地坐落到了椅子上。 

3. QUANT The bulk of something is most of it. 大部分 [QUANT 'of' def-n] 

例： The bulk of the text is essentially a review of these original documents. 正文的大部分基本上是对这些原始文献的回顾。 

4. PRON Bulk is also a pronoun. 大部分 

例： They come from all over the world, though the bulk is from the Indian subcontinent. 他们来自世界各地，但其中大部分人还是来自印度次大陆。 

5. PHRASE If you buy or sell something in bulk , you buy or sell it in large quantities. 大批地 (买卖) 

例： Buying in bulk is more economical than shopping for small quantities. 大批采购比少量购买更经济实惠。

</div>

